Section 2 - ES6 - Javascript New features
1 - Introduction
Javascript is also known as ECMAScript.
The newest version of ECMAScript or ES is ES6.
A lot of the newest features are not supported by a lot of browsers, the instructor goes through a list of
newer functions and uses a site called caniuse to see what functions are supported by which browser.
A high level view of the lectures which are to follow is also given.
BabelJS a site which allows for side by side comparison of the different version of Javascript is shown as is 
an alternative called typescript.

